<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-709] Fail-Over Endpoints Don&apos;t Switch Back to the Primary Endpoint After a Suspension</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-709</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Start Synapse with sample 53 (fail-over endpoints) &lt;br/&gt;
2. Send some messages and they will be sent to server 1 &lt;br/&gt;
3. Shutdown server1 and Synapse will start sending messages to server2 &lt;br/&gt;
4. Restart server1 and enable the endpoint1 (wait till it becomes active again or use JMX) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Synapse will not start sending traffic to server1.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
